Shell - An Interface to interact Kernel. or  A user interface for interacting with Kernel and Commands

Shell types - Unix (bsh - Bourne Shell, csh - C Shell, ksh - Korn shell)
	      Linux (bash - Bourne again shell)

man - Manual (Documentation)


Linux Commands
--------------

Prompt 
username@hostname ~]$      
~ - Tilde / Tilder	 -  Home Directory

$ - bash prompt or user
# - superuser or root or su


Linux is case sensitive 

$ clear		- Clears the screen
$ cal		- Displays calendar
$ ls 	- list of file / directories
$ ls -l - lists in long form	(Shortcut is ll)
$ echo
$ pwd 	- Present Working Directory
$ who - display active users logged on
$whoami  - displays current user name
$ hostname - displays name of the host


Creating Directory
------------------
mkdir - Creates Directory
cd    - Change Directory
cd ..	- Go back to your previous folder
rmdir  - Remove Directory

sleep - delays the cursor
touch - Creates Empty files

cp - copy file(source to destination)
mv - Moves file (from source to destination)
rm - removes files (From Source)


